(1393, 4, '2014-10-14 17:15:15', '2014-10-14 17:15:15', 'Mixed Competition ''14 is slowly getting closer. After the summer holidays there will another chance for WAF to show that we''re one of the best mixed teams of the country. The dates for the mixed season are September 7th and 21st as well as October 12th. Please fill in this <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0ApjaowS75L8bdDhlZEpkVHVKNUczMGFwZXFkT1N6WHc&amp;usp=drive_web#gid=0">document</a> (google docs) to let us know if you''re able to join.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'WAF Mixed ''14', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '621-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-14 17:15:15', '2014-10-14 17:15:15', '', 621, 'http://localhost:8888/621-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1394, 4, '2014-10-14 17:16:36', '2014-10-14 17:16:36', 'As some of you may or may not remember, a year ago several Waffies made a succesful venture selling waffles at Windmill Windup, the largest Ultimate tournament of Europe and they were generous enough to offer the money to our association. A while ago we made survey of different options to choose what to spend the money on. These options were split into two categories, which were communal items on one hand and activities and personal items on the other hand. You could choose two of both categories. Here we would like to share your choices!\r\n\r\nThe options for communal items were:\r\n- Waf flag\r\n- Books and DVDs of Ultimate\r\n- Yellow training vests\r\n- Speaker on wheels\r\n- Bag of misprinted discs\r\n- Brewing WAF beer\r\n\r\nThe activity or personal item options were:\r\n- Barbecue\r\n- WAF socks\r\n- WAF sunglasses\r\n- Visiting pubs\r\n- Personalized WAF pillow covers\r\n\r\nFrom the survey we have obtained the following results:\r\n<strong>Communal items: Waf flag + Books and DVDs of Ultimate</strong>\r\n<strong> Activity/personal items: Barbecue + Personalized WAF pillow covers</strong>\r\n\r\nSome of these things are already being taken care of by the activity committee such as the barbecue. However, if you would like to contribute to realizing any of the other choices, don''t hesitate to let the board know!', 'Waffle money', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '613-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-14 17:16:36', '2014-10-14 17:16:36', '', 613, 'http://localhost:8888/613-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1395, 4, '2014-10-14 17:17:58', '2014-10-14 17:17:58', '<span style="color: #141823;">Love at First Flight (LAFF) is a tournament for starting teams/players and will start with a welcome party on Friday the 8th of August, running through the weekend with games on Saturday and Sunday (9&amp;10 August).</span><br style="color: #141823;" /><br style="color: #141823;" /><span style="color: #141823;">There will be an open, a mixed and a women division! We''ll play 5 vs 5 on lush fields of grass of 75m by 25m. Guys can have max 3 years of exper</span><span class="text_exposed_show" style="color: #141823;">ience. There is no restriction for female players.</span>\r\n\r\nPlayerfee: 40\r\nTeamfee: 100\r\n\r\nThe player fee includes a welcome drink at the welcome party on Friday evening, breakfast on Saturday and Sunday, a sandwich lunch on Saturday and Sunday, dinner on Saturday evening, 2 six-packs of water per team, and player gift.\r\n\r\nWe''re still looking for people to join us for this tournament! You can sign up at either on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/313928248757377/">facebook</a>or by sending an e-mail tothe board.\r\n\r\nFor more information, you can check out the LAFF <a href="http://laff.diabolicheaven.be/">website</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'WAF is going to Love at First Flight!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '603-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-14 17:17:58', '2014-10-14 17:17:58', '', 603, 'http://localhost:8888/603-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1396, 4, '2014-10-14 17:19:30', '2014-10-14 17:19:30', '<div style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: tahoma, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: tahoma, sans-serif;">On Thursday, 22nd of May 2014, the Old Frisbee Republic stroke back!\r\nWAFs introduction tournament, the Ultimate Intergalactic Frisbee Experience, held at the Bongerd, saw many happy faces and some exciting catches, throws and even lay-outs.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: tahoma, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: tahoma, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: tahoma, sans-serif;">And we caught most of it on camera!</span></span></span>If you liked the IFO experience with WAFfies, come join us at one of our trainings (Tue, 20.00, Thu, 19.00) and<a href="http://localhost:8888/index.php/training" target="_blank">see here</a>for more info.</div>\r\n<div style="color: #000000;"></div>', 'Frisbee photographs from Space!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '594-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-14 17:19:30', '2014-10-14 17:19:30', '', 594, 'http://localhost:8888/594-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
